        public Class<?> getCallerClass()
        Description copied from interface: CallerFinder
        Gets the class calling a method.
        Equivalent to CallerFinder.getCallerClass(int) with parameter 3.

        Example:
        A third party class (the caller) calls your API method. In your API method, use this method to get the caller.
        Specified by:
        getCallerClass in interface CallerFinder
        Returns:
        the caller of the method you're using this method in

        Description copied from interface: CallerFinder
        Gets the caller class with a specified level of depth.
        0: returns this class
        1: returns your class
        2: returns the class which called your class
        ... and so on
